column5: Hey folks though I'd share our results thus far from last fall to today.... Put a little slide show / video together for you all....  It's a large file 30 some Mb!!! Hope you like it ENJOY Leechman  Fall 2008 to Present...
So far so good Jacques you need to add some  november  Quinte Walleye to that video.
Great report Jacques.............Don't forget Muskie season is just around the corner.   Thanks for sharing......More good times to come
Thanks Mike!!!  Yes Quinte eyes would be great and also Ottawa R. muskie   Thanks Paul!!! Yes it's getting near ski time for sure   Thanks Dan!!!
video says it all....good tune ...good friends ...good fishing ...good times all add up to a GOOD LIFE.....good on ya'll  Stealing your catch phrase " thanks for sharing "
nicely done, looks like you had a great year!
loved it... thanks for putting it together and sharing it with us.  the hogs at the end were great!

Great work jaques!  I forgot about that white fish!  WHAT A BEAST that was!   close to 5 lbs!   and those LMB at the end!  im dumbfounded! speachless.  that video made me realise how the fishery is good in these neck of the woods!
You just had to post pics 3-5 didnt ya.LOL  Very nice collection of pics jaques  Great tune also.  TFS
Wow, looks impressive man. Hey be sure to watch my video in the report im working up atm...you were of mention...I caught a nice bass buddy!!  Thanks for sharing! MTBF
Thanks Twocoda!!!   Thanks alphaalpha!!! It sure was and it's not over yet!   Thanks frozen-fire!!!   Thanks Kev!!!  Yes we have it pretty good up here!   Thanks Brian!!!   Thanks Mike!!!

Btw, that video may of inspired me to make my own slideshow to reflect on the many fish that have been caught this year.  Or, I could wait and do a 2009 in review video like the other 200+ members do at the end of the year lol
Thanks Mike!!!  Looking forward to seeing your year end review in a slide show

Fantastic stuff Jacques...lol....starts off like a "snuff film"...lol....guess i'm not a hunter....YET.  Lots of memories in there.....good stuff man!   PS...still liking those tip up things you spent so long perfecting!
What web site or program did you use for you slideshow?
Nicely done! Some really good fish porn:)
Awesome stuff....Now that's good porn!!!!!  Thanx bro..  Will
Nice job on the slideshow there Leechman. Didn't the other amigo's catch monster brook trout this spring? Lot's of good fishing up that way. Thanks for this!

Thanks Simon and Welcome back!!! Yes I still like the last tip-ups I made.... they are well balanced and light. How was your trip to France btw??  Wouldn't mind seeing a report of your trip   I use Windows Movie Maker that comes with XP SP2.   Thanks Dusky!!!   Thanks Will!!!   Thanks ehg!!!  Yes the other 2 amigos caught monster specks but did not have the pics on my camera.... that is why they are not in this slideshow.
Nice rack on your Buck!  Good way to fill the freezer.  I like the shot placement    How long was the shot??

Thanks F to the Is-H!!!  That buck came onto the dirt road 400 yards away from me and made it's way at 60 yards and stopped to look behind him, that is when I raised the scope about half an inch and pulled the drigger for the kill in the neck.  It was the only target I had from my position in the tree stand because he was facing me.  He never even saw or smelled me.... Dropped him right in his tracks on the side of the road.... Biggest buck harvested for me and easiest to put on the truck tail gate  Here is a picture from my tree stand.... Looking at the dirt road, the fartest you can see is where he came onto it and started walking toward me in no hurry..... this is when I grabbed my 303, took the safety off and waited patiently    in front of the jimmy there's a hump and below the hump is where he stopped and look behind him
